{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RChaPjz9EVFRCfwBR3PX84","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EgaKiVbd9KxWzWyaL1L2rg","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n demo create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"# ingress-nginx Controller Upgrade Change/Migration Plan\n\n## Current State (as-found, $(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%MZ))\n\n### Controller\n- **Version**: v1.14.1\n- **Image**: registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47\n- **Replicas**: 1\n- **Namespace**: ingress-nginx\n- **Deployment**: ingress-nginx-controller (generation 2 — was patched post-install)\n- **Strategy**: RollingUpdate, maxUnavailable: 1\n- **terminationGracePeriodSeconds**: 0 (non-default; see note below)\n\n### Non-Default Controller Args\nThe following args deviate from a stock ingress-nginx install:\n\n1. \\`--watch-ingress-without-class=true\\` — present in the original last-applied manifest\n2. \\`--watch-ingress-without-class=false\\` — added in a later patch (generation 2)\n\n   **CONFLICT**: both flags are present in the live pod spec. NGINX ingress reads the\n   last occurrence, so the effective value is \\`false\\`. This must be resolved during\n   upgrade by removing the first occurrence and keeping only \\`--watch-ingress-without-class=false\\`.\n\n3. \\`--publish-status-address=localhost\\` — set for kind/bare-metal clusters where no\n   cloud LoadBalancer provides a real IP. Retain unless the cluster gains a real LB.\n\n### ConfigMap (ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller)\nEmpty (no data keys). All nginx tuning is currently at upstream defaults.\nNo custom values need to be carried forward.\n\n### IngressClass\n- Name: \\`nginx\\`\n- Controller: \\`k8s.io/ingress-nginx\\`\n- Must survive the upgrade unchanged.\n\n### Services\n- \\`ingress-nginx-controller\\` (LoadBalancer): 80:30970/TCP, 443:32624/TCP\n- \\`ingress-nginx-controller-admission\\` (ClusterIP): 443/TCP\n\n### Validating Admission Webhook\n- Name: \\`ingress-nginx-admission\\`\n- Endpoint: \\`ingress-nginx-controller-admission.ingress-nginx.svc\\`\n- caBundle is injected by the post-install admission job (Job: ingress-nginx-admission-patch).\n  Must be re-run or the webhook CA must be re-patched after upgrading.\n\n### demo Namespace\n- Ingress resources: **none** (no Ingress objects exist at planning time).\n  No per-Ingress annotation migration is needed.\n- Workloads: \\`demo-app\\` deployment (1 replica), \\`curl-test\\` pod.\n\n---\n\n## Upgrade Steps\n\n### Step 1 — Pre-Upgrade Snapshot\nBefore touching anything, capture current state for rollback reference:\n\n\\`\\`\\`\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > /tmp/ingress-deploy-backup.yaml\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx get configmap ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > /tmp/ingress-cm-backup.yaml\nkubectl get ingressclass nginx -o yaml > /tmp/ingressclass-backup.yaml\nkubectl get validatingwebhookconfiguration ingress-nginx-admission -o yaml > /tmp/webhook-backup.yaml\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 2 — Resolve the Duplicate --watch-ingress-without-class Flag\nThe live spec contains two conflicting occurrences of this flag. Before (or as part of)\nthe image upgrade, patch the Deployment args to contain exactly one occurrence:\n\n\\`\\`\\`\n# Remove the first (=true) entry; keep only --watch-ingress-without-class=false\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx patch deploy ingress-nginx-controller --type=json -p='[\n  {\\\"op\\\": \\\"replace\\\", \\\"path\\\": \\\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/args\\\",\n   \\\"value\\\": [\n     \\\"/nginx-ingress-controller\\\",\n     \\\"--election-id=ingress-nginx-leader\\\",\n     \\\"--controller-class=k8s.io/ingress-nginx\\\",\n     \\\"--ingress-class=nginx\\\",\n     \\\"--configmap=$(POD_NAMESPACE)/ingress-nginx-controller\\\",\n     \\\"--validating-webhook=:8443\\\",\n     \\\"--validating-webhook-certificate=/usr/local/certificates/cert\\\",\n     \\\"--validating-webhook-key=/usr/local/certificates/key\\\",\n     \\\"--watch-ingress-without-class=false\\\",\n     \\\"--publish-status-address=localhost\\\"\n   ]}\n]'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nVerify only one occurrence of the flag remains in the live pod spec after rollout.\n\n### Step 3 — (Recommended) Increase terminationGracePeriodSeconds\nThe Deployment currently sets \\`terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0\\`, which kills the pod\nimmediately on eviction/rolling-update without waiting for the preStop (\\`/wait-shutdown\\`)\nhook to complete. Upstream recommends >= 300 s so in-flight connections can drain:\n\n\\`\\`\\`\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx patch deploy ingress-nginx-controller --type=strategic -p \\\n  '{\\\"spec\\\":{\\\"template\\\":{\\\"spec\\\":{\\\"terminationGracePeriodSeconds\\\":300}}}}'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nApply this change *before* the image upgrade so any rolling update during the upgrade\nalready benefits from graceful draining.\n\n### Step 4 — Upgrade the Controller Image\nReplace the image tag and digest. Obtain the new version's sha256 digest from the\nofficial release notes at https://github.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/releases.\n\nExample (replace X.Y.Z and <new-digest> with the target release values):\n\n\\`\\`\\`\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx set image deploy/ingress-nginx-controller \\\n  controller=registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:vX.Y.Z@sha256:<new-digest>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nAlso update the version labels on the Deployment and its pod template:\n\n\\`\\`\\`\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx patch deploy ingress-nginx-controller --type=strategic -p \\\n  '{\\\"metadata\\\":{\\\"labels\\\":{\\\"app.kubernetes.io/version\\\":\\\"X.Y.Z\\\"}},\n    \\\"spec\\\":{\\\"template\\\":{\\\"metadata\\\":{\\\"labels\\\":{\\\"app.kubernetes.io/version\\\":\\\"X.Y.Z\\\"}}}}}'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 5 — Renew the Admission Webhook CA Bundle\nAfter the controller pod starts on the new image, re-run the admission patch Job\n(or delete and let the post-upgrade Helm hook recreate it) so the ValidatingWebhookConfiguration\ngets a fresh caBundle signed by the new certificates:\n\n\\`\\`\\`\n# If installed via Helm:\nhelm -n ingress-nginx upgrade ingress-nginx ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx ...\n\n# If installed via static manifests, delete the old admission job and re-apply:\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx delete job ingress-nginx-admission-create ingress-nginx-admission-patch --ignore-not-found\nkubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/controller-vX.Y.Z/deploy/static/provider/kind/deploy.yaml\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nVerify the webhook is healthy:\n\\`\\`\\`\nkubectl get validatingwebhookconfiguration ingress-nginx-admission -o jsonpath='{.webhooks[0].clientConfig.caBundle}' | base64 -d | openssl x509 -noout -dates\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 6 — Review Release Notes for Breaking Changes\nBefore applying, check the upstream changelog for any:\n- Removed or renamed ConfigMap keys (none currently set, so low risk)\n- Removed or renamed Ingress annotations (no Ingress objects in demo namespace — low risk)\n- RBAC / CRD changes (apply updated ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding manifests if any)\n- Kubernetes version compatibility matrix changes\n\nReference: https://github.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/blob/main/Changelog.md\n\n### Step 7 — Post-Upgrade Validation\n\n\\`\\`\\`\n# Confirm new pod is Running\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n\n# Confirm reported version\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx exec deploy/ingress-nginx-controller -- /nginx-ingress-controller --version\n\n# Confirm only one --watch-ingress-without-class flag in args\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx get pod -l app.kubernetes.io/component=controller -o jsonpath='{.items[0].spec.containers[0].args}' | tr ',' '\\n' | grep watch-ingress\n\n# Confirm webhook accepts Ingress objects\nkubectl -n demo apply --dry-run=server -f - <<EOF\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Ingress\nmetadata:\n  name: smoke-test\nspec:\n  ingressClassName: nginx\n  rules:\n  - host: smoke.example.com\n    http:\n      paths:\n      - path: /\n        pathType: Prefix\n        backend:\n          service:\n            name: demo-app\n            port:\n              number: 80\nEOF\n\n# Confirm HTTP traffic still reaches demo-app through the controller\nkubectl -n demo exec curl-test -- curl -s -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}' http://\\$(kubectl -n ingress-nginx get svc ingress-nginx-controller -o jsonpath='{.spec.clusterIP}')/ -H 'Host: smoke.example.com'\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## Rollback Plan\n\nIf the new image causes failures:\n\n\\`\\`\\`\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx apply -f /tmp/ingress-deploy-backup.yaml\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx apply -f /tmp/webhook-backup.yaml\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Non-Default Settings to Preserve\n\n| Setting | Current Value | Action |\n|---|---|---|\n| --publish-status-address | localhost | Retain |\n| --watch-ingress-without-class | false (effective) | Retain; remove duplicate =true entry |\n| terminationGracePeriodSeconds | 0 | **Increase to 300** before upgrade |\n| ingress-nginx-controller ConfigMap | empty | No migration needed |\n| IngressClass nginx | k8s.io/ingress-nginx | No change needed |\n| NodePort 30970/32624 | set by Service | Preserved automatically |\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap in demo namespace"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2110,"cache_read_input_tokens":39024,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2110},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2c190e30-0d5d-4af8-a473-4972a1fea71e","uuid":"525a1e76-6aa9-4827-9646-2e4c1d8c0e7c","request_id":"req_011CcMNoe9B5Yi5